    Animate
    An API for creating an Animation and defining how it should be executed.
    Animation
    An animation is a function which is called repeatedly during its lifetime, which is determined by a LifeTime and a StopCondition.
    AnimationState
    The state of an animation at a given point in time.
    BaseStyle
    An immutable, wither-like cloner method based settings class for basic component style properties like background color, foundation color, foreground color and the cursor.

    ComponentDragEventDelegate<C extends javax.swing.JComponent>
    A JComponent and MouseEvent delegate providing useful context information to various Action listeners used by UIForAnySwing.onMouseDrag(Action) like for example the ComponentMouseEventDelegate.mouseX() and ComponentMouseEventDelegate.mouseY() of the event as well as more drag specific information like ComponentDragEventDelegate.dragEvents() and ComponentDragEventDelegate.dragPositions().

    ComponentMouseEventDelegate<C extends javax.swing.JComponent>

    ComponentStyleDelegate<C extends javax.swing.JComponent>

    Implement this functional interface to either paint custom styles on components by registering painters on the style API using methods like
    ComponentStyleDelegate.painter(UI.Layer, Painter) and
    ComponentStyleDelegate.painter(UI.Layer, String, Painter)
    or
    for defining custom animations by registering painters in the animation API using the AbstractDelegate.paint(AnimationState, Painter) method inside of an Animation registered through AbstractDelegate.animateOnce(double, TimeUnit, Animation).
